s I watched her finish year two of pre-K my gut was telling me she just was not ready. It is definitely not the trend where I live to &quot;red shirt&quot; a child. I did not want her experience in kindergarten to be a negative one where she was always feeling she had to play catch up with others. Giving my daughter that year has made her confident in the classroom and is making her kindergarten year a positive one. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="707" language="en" documentId="5352" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="mom of three" date="November 12, 2012 at 11:44 am" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://schoolsofthought.blogs.cnn.com/2012/11/12/my-view-kindergarten-redshirting-different-for-each-child/comment-page-1" topic="redshirting" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="5352" notes="" title="My View: Kindergarten redshirting different for each child"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="707"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>